import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Median delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['delay'], ax=ax, color='lightblue')
    ax.axvline(x=data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['delay'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the average delay time for flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Delay Time (minutes)')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='distance', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['distance'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight distances?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['delay', 'distance_range']]
    data = data.groupby(['distance_range']).mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='distance_range', y='delay', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.axhline(y=data['delay'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Delay')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Distance Range')
    plt.ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.title('How does distance range affect flight delays?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
